  "response_text": "For someone with a gluten allergy, it's essential to avoid foods that contain gluten, a protein found in wheat, barley, and rye. Here's a sample 7-day meal plan that excludes gluten:\n\n**Monday**\n\n* Breakfast: Gluten-free oatmeal with fresh fruits and nuts\n* Lunch: Grilled chicken breast with roasted vegetables (such as bell peppers, carrots, and zucchini) and quinoa\n* Dinner: Baked salmon with sweet potato and green beans\n\n**Tuesday**\n\n* Breakfast: Scrambled eggs with spinach and gluten-free toast made from rice flour\n* Lunch: Turkey lettuce wraps with avocado, tomato, and mustard (make sure the mustard is gluten-free)\n* Dinner: Grilled steak with roasted Brussels sprouts and brown rice\n\n**Wednesday**\n\n* Breakfast: Smoothie bowl with almond milk, banana, and almond butter topping (use gluten-free granola)\n* Lunch: Chicken Caesar salad with gluten-free croutons made from rice flour\n* Dinner: Grilled chicken breast with roasted asparagus and quinoa\n\n**Thursday**\n\n* Breakfast: Gluten-free pancakes made from rice flour and topped with fresh fruits and maple syrup\n* Lunch: Grilled chicken breast with mixed greens and a citrus vinaigrette dressing (make sure the dressing is gluten-free)\n* Dinner: Shrimp and vegetable stir-fry with brown rice\n\n**Friday**\n\n* Breakfast: Gluten-free waffles made from corn flour and topped with fresh fruits and whipped cream\n* Lunch: Turkey and avocado wrap with gluten-free tortilla made from corn flour\n* Dinner: Grilled chicken breast with roasted broccoli and quinoa\n\n**Saturday**\n\n* Breakfast: Breakfast burrito with scrambled eggs, black beans, and gluten-free tortilla made from corn flour\n* Lunch: Grilled chicken breast with mixed greens and a gluten-free balsamic vinaigrette dressing\n* Dinner: Baked chicken thighs with roasted carrots and brown rice\n\n**Sunday**\n\n* Breakfast: Gluten-free French toast made from rice flour and topped with fresh fruits and maple syrup\n* Lunch: Chicken and quinoa bowl with roasted vegetables and a gluten-free tahini sauce\n* Dinner: Grilled salmon with roasted asparagus and quinoa\n\n**Snacks**\n\n* Fresh fruits and nuts\n* Gluten-free energy bars\n* Popcorn made from gluten-free corn kernels\n* Gluten-free crackers with hummus or guacamole\n\n**Tips**\n\n* Always read labels to ensure that the ingredients are gluten-free.\n* Be cautious of cross-contamination with gluten-containing foods in the kitchen.\n* Explore different types of gluten-free flours, such as rice flour, corn flour, and almond flour, to add variety to your meals.\n* Consider consulting with a registered dietitian or a healthcare professional for personalized dietary advice.\n\nRemember, a gluten-free diet can be healthy and delicious with a little creativity and planning.",
